sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K658002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: a bacteria population-control device with RBS0.6 driven by lacl+pL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The device is a twin part of Biobrick part BBa_K658001. This device is made up of three subparts: a LuxI produce, a LuxR producer and a killer protein producer. It is designed to build a programmed bacterial death circuit, which is based on the quorum sensing system of Vibrio fischeri. iGEM-Team XMU-China has designed a series of bacteria population-control devices using RBSs of different strength in the killer protein producer. This device has the ability to maintain cell density of the bacteria population at a relatively low value compared with bacteria without this circuit and extends the stable stage. RBS0.6 was used to regulate the expression of killer protein ccdB.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zhizhen Zhao
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This device is a twin part of BBa_K658001.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Design considerations are the same as Biobrick part BBa_K658001.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lacI+pL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The PLlac 0-1 promoter is a hybrid regulatory region consisting of the promoter P(L) of phage lambda with the cI binding sites replaced with lacO1. The hybrid design allows for strong promotion that can nevertheless be tightly repressed by LacI, the Lac inhibitor (i.e. repressor) (BBa_C0010) ([LUTZ97]). The activity of the promoter can be regulated over a >600-fold range by IPTG in E.Coli DH5-alpha-Z1 (same paper reference).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Neelaksh Varshney, Grace Kenney, Daniel Shen, Samantha Sutton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
hybrid promoter design to create strong promoter that is, at the same time, highly repressible. note that the upstream operator installed in this hybrid is slightly different than the one in the original source (Lutz and Bujard, 1997). the most upstream operator region is slightly truncated in the represillator version, so that both operators in the hybrid are the same sequence. see references for details. also, the sequence has been truncated after the transcriptional start site.

LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and increase transcription. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS based on Elowitz repressilator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: luxI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Synthesizes 3OC6HSL, which binds to LuxR.

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the Lux repressor, LuxR. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the signalling compound HSL. This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: An LVA tail (sequence: AANDENYALVA) was added to increase protein degradation. .

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K322123
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Phycobilin is chromophores (light-capturing molecules) found in cyanobacteria and in the chloroplasts of red algae, glaucophytes and some cryptomonads (though not in green algae and higher plants)， used in light sensor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French and Richard Edward Partridge-Hicks
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is derived from K098010 but PCR was used to remove the terminator, so that cph8 could be added at the end of the operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The actual forward sequence has the same changes at the start as seen in clone H11 described above. The reverse sequence is as expected. Features same as for the one above apart from the terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K322124
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Red light sensor Cph8 (from Coliroid) with RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Cph8 is a combination of cph1 and envZ which, together with PCB, form a transmembrane, histidine kinase-based light sensing system. It contains the photoreceptor from Cph1 and the histidine kinase and response-regulator from EnvZ???OmpR, producing a particularly strongresponse to light.
Features: cph8 coding sequence 16 to 2250, RBS 6 to 10.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French and Richard Edward Partridge-Hicks
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: BBa_I15010　(Photosensing Chimaera (Cph8) (not working, but amplified out of the whole construct))
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Notes: we were unable to revive BioBrick I15010 with the coding sequence of the cph8 red light sensor fusion protein, so we sought to amplify it from BioBrick BBa_M30109. This led to numerous problems. It is clear from the Registry sequence data that M30109 is not what it is supposed to be. It does include cph8 with a ribosome binding site, but the RBS is not joined to cph8 by a standard scar; promoter R0040 may be present, but there appears to be an EcoRI site a little upstream of the ribosome binding site so that, when we cloned our PCR product, we failed to recover the promoter region; also the PstI site in cph8, which was mutated out in I15010, is still present in the version in M30109. We therefore performed corrective PCR to obtain a clone with the correct prefix, a ribosome binding site, and the cph8 coding sequence with the PstI site properly removed, which we present here, cloned in pSB1C3.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is taken from the upstream region of ompC. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the three operator sites and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The promoter includes the three OmpR binding sites: C1, C2, and C3. The promoter starts at -107 and goes up to the transcriptional start site at +1.
An alternate version, BBa_R0083, cuts out the C2 and C3 sites.
The efficacy of this promoter versus the truncated ompC upstream region (BBa_R0083) or the ompF upstream region (BBa_R0084) is currently unknown.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lacZa-ccdB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A fusion protein of lacZalpha(I732006) and ccdB(K145151). It should have the function of ccdB to cause E. coli cells to die, but have less toxicity because of the lacZalpha part. It should also have the function of lacZalpha as a reporter for measurement. This part is similar to J32026 but the multiple cloning sites are eliminated. It is constructed by PCR from the plasmid pluxCcdB3(a gift from Prof. Lingchong You).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zongxiao He, Hao Jiang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PCR from the plasmid pluxCcdB3(a gift from Prof. Lingchong You). Forward Primer: GTTTCT TCTAG ATG accatgattacgg attcactggccgtcgttttac Reverse Primer: GTTTCTTC CTGCAG CGGCCGC T ACTAGT A TTATTA tattccccagaacatcaggtta Digest with XbaI and SpeI, ligate into pSB1A3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The part is similar to BBa_J32026 and the original coding sequence in pluxCcdB3, but the multiple cloning sites are eliminated in order to avoid site-specific mutagenesis. The multiple cloning sites are from lacZalpha in pZErO-2.
After eliminate the MCS, the lacZalpha part is identical to the N-terminal of the wild type gene(BBa_I732006 & BBa_I732005), and fused with the ccdB part (BBa_K145151) with a 3aa linker.
